165	\begin{definition}\leanok
166	[Short complex of free sheaves]
167	  \label{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex}
168	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_shortComplex}
169	  
170	  In the setting of Lemma~REF, define the short complex of sheaves of \(k\)-modules
171	  \[
172	    \mathcal F_1 \xrightarrow{\;f\;} \mathcal F_2 \oplus \mathcal F_3 \xrightarrow{\;g\;} \mathcal F_4,
173	  \]
174	  where \(f\) is the biproduct lift of the two maps induced by \(X_1 \to X_2\) and \(-X_1 \to X_3\), and \(g\) is the biproduct desc of the two maps induced by \(X_2 \to X_4\) and \(X_3 \to X_4\). The composition \(g \circ f = 0\) follows from the cokernel-cofork condition of the pushout.
